#. REF: nya18, pts-vp-pli1.316, sc17
msgctxt "mn46:18.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, tittakālābu visena saṃsaṭṭho. "
msgstr "Suppose there was some bitter gourd mixed with poison. "

msgctxt "mn46:18.2"
msgid "Atha puriso āgaccheyya jīvitukāmo amaritukāmo sukhakāmo dukkhappaṭikūlo. "
msgstr "Then a man would come along who wants to live and doesn’t want to die, who wants to be happy and recoils from pain. "

msgctxt "mn46:18.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "They’d say to him: "

msgctxt "mn46:18.4"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, ayaṃ tittakālābu visena saṃsaṭṭho, "
msgstr "‘Here, mister, this is bitter gourd mixed with poison. "

#. VAR: piva → pipa (si, pts1)
msgctxt "mn46:18.5"
msgid "sace ākaṅkhasi piva. "
msgstr "Drink it if you like. "

#. VAR: pivitvā → pītvā (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: pivato → pipato (si, pts1)
msgctxt "mn46:18.6"
msgid "Tassa te pivato ceva nacchādessati vaṇṇenapi gandhenapi rasenapi, pivitvā ca pana maraṇaṃ vā nigacchasi maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhan’ti. "
msgstr "If you drink it, the color, aroma, and flavor will be unappetizing, and it will result in death or deadly pain.’ "

msgctxt "mn46:18.7"
msgid "So taṃ appaṭisaṅkhāya piveyya, nappaṭinissajjeyya. "
msgstr "He wouldn’t reject it. Without reflection, he’d drink it. "

msgctxt "mn46:18.8"
msgid "Tassa taṃ pivato ceva nacchādeyya vaṇṇenapi gandhenapi rasenapi, pivitvā ca pana maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ. "
msgstr "The color, aroma, and flavor would be unappetizing, and it would result in death or deadly pain. "

msgctxt "mn46:18.9"
msgid "Tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ vadāmi, yamidaṃ dhammasamādānaṃ paccuppannadukkhañceva āyatiñca dukkhavipākaṃ. (1) "
msgstr "This is comparable to the way of taking up practices that is painful now and results in future pain, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya19, sc18
